// visibility of variables in javascript
// there are three types of scopes in javascript
// 1.global scopes
// 2.function scopes
// 3.block scopes

// global scope :
//               global scope is the outermost scope in javascript.variables and function can be accessible anywhere in the function.
//               example :
//             //   var x = 10 ;
//              function example(){
//             //   console.log(x);}
//            console .log(x);
//             example(); it will print 10 10

// function scopes  
//              function copes are visible within the function

// 
// block scope              
//            visibility of variable within a block of codes that are enclosed within{}
